main event: A witness in Munster, Indiana observed 6 orange-colored objects traveling northward at a high speed and exhibiting high maneuverability in 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as moving quite fast and being highly maneuverable, consistent with common UFO reports.
The analyst was unable to determine a meaningful explanation for the sighting.
The witness reported that the objects appeared to emit a beam or shaft of light that was directed at a small area on the ground.
After the objects disappeared, the witness noticed that the vegetation in the area where the beam of light was directed seemed to be pressed down or flattened.
The witness considered this one of the most interesting UFO sightings in the area, lasting 2-3 minutes.
